{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place jalapeño, red onion, cilantro, cumin, paprika, salt and pepper into mixing bowl and chop <nobr>3 sec\/speed 7<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add salmon, lime juice and avocado oil and mix <nobr>2 sec\/\/speed 3<\/nobr>. Transfer ceviche into a bowl and place into refrigerator to allow flavors to infuse for 10 minutes.","Cut watermelon into ¼ inch slices, then using a round cookie cutter, cut out 20-25 watermelon rounds. Transfer rounds onto a serving platter.","Placing the cookie cutter back over the watermelon round to use as a mold, spoon 1 tsp of salmon ceviche onto the watermelon and spread out to the edges (this ensures a neat shape). Carefully remove cookie cutter and repeat with remaining watermelon rounds and ceviche.","Garnish with avocado and a few drops Tabasco sauce for each ceviche stack and serve immediately."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["1 fresh jalapeño chili, stem and seeds removed","1 oz red onion, cut into pieces","4 sprigs cilantro, leaves only","&frac18; tsp ground cumin","&frac18; tsp paprika","&frac18; tsp salt","&frac18; tsp ground black pepper","9 oz fresh salmon fillets, skinless, cut into pieces (¼ in.)","1 oz lime juice","2 tsp avocado oil","28 - 30 oz watermelon (approx. ¼ watermelon)","½ avocado, flesh only, cubed (¼ in.)","Tabasco sauce, to taste (optional)"]}],"id":"r109208","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-Grt-aO5J9Zc\/XZMv1YHOxBI\/AAAAAAAAaWw\/x6jEa-8ebkwIlVCQxCgJln4ICPhJNDvWgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_qoUJBB7XCDV5ERpP.png","title":"Watermelon and Salmon Ceviche Stack","publishedAt":"2017-08-11T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"3.2 g","fat":"2.8 g","uom":"per 1 piece","carbohydrates":"2.8 g","calories":"209 kJ \/ 49 kcal"},"usefulItems":"cookie cutter (approx. 1 in.), serving platter, refrigerator","hintsAndTricks":["This dish is best served immediately, however you can cut out the watermelon rounds in advance and store in the refrigerator for 1-2 hours before making the salmon ceviche. It is not advisable to prepare the ceviche component in advance as citric acid in the lime juice may overcook the salmon."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","30m","25 pieces"]}